message.content: Recall that the ceiling function $\lceil x\rceil$ means to find the least integer that is greater than or equal to $x$. In this case, there are two integers that are both greater than or equal to $-2.4$: $-2$ and $-1$. However, the least integer is $-2$, so $\lceil -2.4\rceil = \boxed{-2}$.
